quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  2,127,"And as Ibrahim raised up the foundations of the Home and Ismail (with him), (saying), \"Our Lord, (graciously) accept (this) from us. Surely You, Ever You, are The Ever-Hearing, The Ever-Knowing"
  2,128,"Our Lord, and make us (both) Muslims (i.e. surrendered) to You, and of our offspring a nation Muslim to You, and show us our rituals and relent towards us; surely You Ever You are The Superbly Relenting, The Ever-Merciful"
  2,129,"Our Lord, and send forth among them a Messenger, (one) of them, who (will) recite to them Your ayat (Signs verses) and teach them the Book, and (the) Wisdom, and cleanse them; surely You, Ever You, are The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Wise"
  2,130,"And whoever desirously shirks from the creed of Ibrahim (Abraham) except he who befools himself? And indeed We have already elected him in the present (life), (Literally: the lowly, i.e., the life of this world) and surely in the Hereafter he is indeed among the righteous"
  2,131,"As his Lord said to him, \"Surrender, \" (i.e., be muslim) he said, \"I have surrendered to The Lord of the worlds"
  2,132,"And Ibrahim (Abraham) enjoined his seeds (Or. sons) with this, and (also) Yaaqub, (Jacob) (saying), \"O my seeds! Surely Allah has elected for you the religion; so, definitely do not die except (while) you are Muslims"
  2,133,"Or (even) were you witnesses as death was present to Yaaqub? (Jacob) As he said to his seeds' (Or. sons) \"What will you worship even after me?\" They said, \" We will worship your God and the God of your fathers Ibrahim, Shuaayb and Ishaq, (Abraham, Ishmael and Isaac, respectively) One God; and to Him we are Muslims.\" (i.e., to Him we surrender)"
  2,134,"That is a nation (that) has already passed away; it shall have whatever it earned, and you shall have whatever you have earned, and you shall not be questioned about whatever they were doing"